[[Glasgow]], the largest city in [[Scotland]], supports a large number of active [[amateur dramatics]] and [[musical theatre]] companies. Some of the larger companies use the professional stages at the [[King's Theatre, Glasgow|King's Theatre]], [[Theatre Royal, Glasgow|Theatre Royal]] and [[Pavilion Theatre (Glasgow)|The Pavilion]], and in the past the [[Alhambra Theatre]]. The [[Mitchell Library|Mitchell Theatre]], run by [[Glasgow City Council]], is one of the most popularly used theatres for amateur companies, as is the [[Eastwood Park Theatre]] operated in the south side.

==Musical theatre companies==
* [http://www.lyricclub.net The Lyric Club] formed in 1902
* [http://www.glasgowlightoperaclub.co.uk/ Glasgow Light Opera Club] (GLOC) originally formed in 1907 as the St Mungo Opera Club.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.glasgowlightoperaclub.co.uk/index.php/7/|title=Our History|website=www.glasgowlightoperaclub.co.uk|language=en|access-date=2017-01-28}}</ref> The Club is now known as the Glasgow Light Opera Club and performs a musical theatre production annually in the [[King's Theatre, Glasgow|King's Theatre]] Glasgow. Since the club's inception in 1907, it has been part of its constitution that it supports charitable [http://www.glasgowlightoperaclub.co.uk/ causes] through its musical endeavours, both locally and internationally.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Glasgow Light opera Club|title=Welcome to our Home Page|website=glasgowlightoperaclub.co.uk}}</ref>
* [[Pantheon Club Glasgow]] formed in 1926, with their first production staged at the Theatre Royal, February 1927  
* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110314172243/http://www.theminervaclub.co.uk/ The Minerva Club] formed in 1927  
* [http://www.newvictoryplayers.org.uk New Victory Players] established in 1945 are based in the South Side of Glasgow with members from all over the city. Productions are both Plays and Musicals.
* [[The Cecilian Society]] formed at Glasgow University in 1952
* [[Theatre Guild Glasgow]] formed in 1960 
* [[The Apollo Players]] formed in 1966 
* [http://www.runwaytheatre.co.uk Runway Theatre Company] founded at Glasgow Airport as the Glasgow Airport Drama Club) in 1967 and renamed in 2007.<ref>https://www.runwaytheatre.co.uk/about/history/</ref>
* [http://www.theatresouthproductions.com Theatre South Productions] formed in 1992
* [[Star-Light Theatre Group]] formed in 2008
* [http://www.madpropstheatre.com Mad Props Theatre] - Glasgow's charitable theatre initiative raising funds for [[Leukaemia & Lymphoma Research]]
* [[Operating Theatre Company]] formed in the medical faculty of Glasgow University

