{{for|the professor|Anne Carlisle (professor)}} {{Infobox person | image = Slava Tsukerman and Anne Carlisle 2017.jpg | image_caption = Slava Tsukerman and Anne Carlisle at a screening of ''Liquid Sky'' at the [[Quad Cinema]], New York City, in 2017 | imagesize = 150px | | name = Anne Carlisle | birth_date = {{birth year and age|1956}} | birth_place = [[United States]] | spouse = Kenneth Master | children = | occupation = [[Actress]], [[writer]], [[artist]] }}
'''Anne Carlisle''' (born 1956) is an American actress, performance artist, acting teacher, author, and model.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://movies.nytimes.com/person/10962/Anne-Carlisle|work=[[The New York Times]]|title=Anne Carlisle}}</ref>
She is known for co-writing and playing both the lead female and male counterpart roles in the film ''[[Liquid Sky]]''.<ref>{{cite web|work=[[The New York Times]]|title='LIQUID SKY,' HIGH FASHION AND A U.F.O.|authorlink=Janet Maslin|first=Janet|last=Maslin|date=July 22, 1983|url=https://movies.nytimes.com/movie/review?res=9E03E0DA143BF931A15754C0A965948260}}</ref> She also played a minor role of "Victoria" in the 1985 [[Susan Seidelman]] film ''[[Desperately Seeking Susan]]'', the [[Transvestites|transvestite]] "Gwendoline" in ''[[Crocodile Dundee]]''<ref>{{cite web|work=AMC|title=Story Notes for Crocodile Dundee|url=http://blogs.amctv.com/movie-blog/2012/09/story-notes-trivia-crocodile-dundee.php|first=Erica|last=Kelly|date=September 20, 2012}}</ref> and starred in an episode of TV series ''[[Miami Vice]]''. Carlisle also adapted and wrote a novel version of her cult, new wave film ''Liquid Sky''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Anne Carlisle|work=Science Fiction Encyclopedia|url=http://www.sf-encyclopedia.com/entry/carlisle_anne}}</ref>
Carlisle posed for ''[[Playboy (magazine)|Playboy]]'' in 1984.<ref>{{cite web|work=[[Playboy (magazine)|Playboy]]|title=Anne Carlisle|url=http://www.playboy.com/girls/view/anne-carlisle}}</ref>
==Liquid Sky 2== In 2014 in an interview with ''[[The Awl]]'' it was confirmed by ''Liquid Sky'' director [[Slava Tsukerman]], a sequel, ''Liquid Sky 2'', was in the works.<ref name=TA>{{cite web|work=[[The Awl]]|url=http://www.theawl.com/2014/02/the-liquid-sky-sequel-is-coming|title=The "Liquid Sky" Sequel Is Coming: A Chat With The Director Of The Best Film About New York|first=James|last=Ramsay|date=February 18, 2014}}</ref> Anne Carlisle would be returning in the sequel in the role of Margaret.<ref name=TA/>
